CSSKeyframeRule.summary: The CSSKeyframeRule interface describes an object representing a set of styles for a given keyframe. It corresponds to the contents of a single keyframe of a @keyframes at-rule.

CSSKeyframeRuleKeyText.summary: The keyText property of the interface represents the keyframe selector as a comma-separated list of percentage values. The from and to keywords map to 0% and 100%, respectively.
